West nile virus encephalitis, equids - Italy 981127001452
Date: Tue, 14 Sep 1999 12:58:35 -0400
From: Marjorie P. Pollack <pollackmp@mindspring.com>
Source: Media report

Thirty-three people in Russia's Volgograd region have died and another 559
have been sickened with meningitis since the outbreak of the epidemic
caused by West Nile virus, officials said on Tuesday.
The infection spreads through mosquitoes, with insects catching it from
water fowl, the officials from Russia's State Sanitary and Epidemiological
Service told [reporters. The virus is mostly found in Africa, but there
are natural contagion areas both in Europe and Russia, they said.
--
