[It may be that West Nile virus infections are comprising an emerging
disease. A spate of recent outbreaks, posted as noted above, as well as a
few cases in the Czech Republic
<http://www.cdc.gov/ncidod/EID/vol5no4/letters.htm#HubÃ¡lek>, may only
reflect better surveillance (doubtful). 559 sick and 33 dead seems like a
huge number of cases of illness caused by this virus in one place at one
time. Can anyone tell us who did the laboratory diagnosis (virus
isolations? serology only?)? Having a virus isolate to sequence would be
epidemiologically useful. Vincent Deubel, Pasteur Institute, Paris, likely
would be interested in obtaining an isolate for such comparisons. - Mod.CHC
